Package: proxmox-lxcri
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, zfsutils-linux (>= 2.1), criu (>= 3.15)
Recommends: proxmox-ve (>= 7.0), containerd (>= 1.6)
Suggests: kubernetes-cni, docker.io
Description: OCI-compatible container runtime for Proxmox VE
 Proxmox LXCRI is a high-performance OCI-compatible runtime implementation
 that transforms Proxmox VE into a container and VM orchestration worker.
 .
 Key features:
  * Revolutionary ZFS checkpoint/restore functionality
  * Lightning-fast filesystem-level snapshots (seconds vs minutes)
  * Hybrid architecture: ZFS snapshots + CRIU fallback
  * Seamless integration with Proxmox VE infrastructure
  * Full OCI Runtime Specification v1.0 compliance
  * Enterprise-grade security and isolation
  * Native ZFS storage management with deduplication
  * Advanced networking with VLAN and SDN support
 .
 This package provides the proxmox-lxcri binary and configuration files
 for running OCI-compliant containers on Proxmox VE using LXC backend
 with revolutionary ZFS checkpoint/restore capabilities.
